In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discussed various topics including healthcare reform, the situation in Afghanistan, H1N1 vaccine distribution, and the President's upcoming meetings. He mentioned that the President's statement on healthcare reform was prompted by endorsements from doctors and the organization representing seniors. Gibbs also addressed concerns about the situation in Afghanistan and the delay in troop pullouts, as well as the distribution of H1N1 vaccines to Wall Street firms and the handling of the vaccine program. He mentioned that the President's meeting with House Democrats tomorrow is to discuss the importance of continuing to make progress on healthcare reform. Gibbs also mentioned that the President's trip to Asia is still planned and that there is a meeting scheduled with the Joint Chiefs of Staff before the trip.